---

## Requirements

- **bash 4.0+** — macOS ships bash 3.2; install a newer one via Homebrew
- A terminal with 256-color support (`TERM=xterm-256color` or equivalent)
- Recommended minimum width: **100 columns** for menu mode

```bash
# macOS — upgrade bash first
brew install bash
```

---

## Install

```bash
git clone https://github.com/shiloenix/zfolio
cd zfolio
./install.sh
```

The installer will:
- Detect your OS and pick the right install directory (`/usr/local/bin` or `/opt/homebrew/bin` on Apple Silicon)
- Request `sudo` only if needed
- Verify the binary landed correctly
- Warn you if the install directory isn't in your `$PATH`

To uninstall:

```bash
./install.sh uninstall
```

---

## Run

```bash
# If installed system-wide
zfolio

# Or directly from the repo
./zfolio
```

On launch you'll be asked to choose a mode.

---

## Modes

### Shell mode

A fake interactive terminal. Type commands like you would in a real shell.

```
zahana@portfolio:~$ whofetch
zahana@portfolio:~$ skills
zahana@portfolio:~$ projects
zahana@portfolio:~$ contact
```

| Command      | Description                        |
|--------------|------------------------------------|
| `whofetch`   | neofetch-style identity card       |
| `about`      | bio and background                 |
| `skills`     | tech stack and expertise           |
| `projects`   | things built                       |
| `experience` | work history                       |
| `contact`    | links and email                    |
| `menu`       | switch to split-pane TUI           |
| `clear`      | clear the screen                   |
| `sudo`       | try it                             |
| `/?`         | show all commands                  |
| `exit`       | quit                               |

### Menu mode

Split-pane TUI. Sidebar on the left, content panel on the right.

```
↑ ↓          navigate sections
1 – 6        jump directly to a section
Esc          return to shell mode
q            quit
```

Type `menu` in shell mode to enter it, or choose `2` at the launch prompt.

---

## Customization

All personal data lives at the top of `zfolio` in clearly labeled variables — no digging through functions required.

```bash
# Identity
NAME="Zahàna"
ROLE_SHORT="Embedded · Cyber · Microelectronics · ML/AI"
ROLE_FULL="Embedded Systems Engineer - ..."
LOCATION="Madagascar"
EMAIL="you@example.com"
GITHUB="github.com/yourhandle"
LINKEDIN="linkedin.com/in/yourprofile"
WEBSITE="yoursite.dev"

# Bio paragraph
ABOUT="Your bio here."

# Skills — format: "Label : value, value, value"
SKILLS=(
  "Languages  : C, C++, Python"
  "Embedded   : Arduino, RTOS, FPGA"
)

# Projects — format: "Name|Description|Stack|Link"
PROJECTS=(
  "Project Name|What it does.|Lang, Framework|yoursite.dev/project"
)

# Experience — format: "Date range|Title|Note"
EXPERIENCE=(
  "2023 – present|Role · Company|One-line summary."
)
```

After editing, no build step — just run `./zfolio`.

